          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb") Sales is a set of processes, management/control, marketing and the human factor, all designed with the primary purpose of demonstrating the value of a company’s products. The processes should be designed to be carried out at a company level, rather than individually, and all the people involved in this task should act in a consistent manner.  Regarding management and control, the use of technology (CRM) is essential for the automation of the sales processes established to improve efficiency (or “to do more with less”), monitoring sales plans more effectively and generating enough information to allow for better market profitability and sales forecasting, while increasing assertiveness when it comes to decision-making in respect of products, strategies, markets, internal sales processes, etc.  In addition, marketing should always be aligned with sales processes, thus ensuring sufficient opportunities to meet the objectives of the Sales Plan.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb") Finally, I also think that most of what is stated above will be of no practical use, unless the human factor is well consolidated.  This is why I firmly believe in a mutually beneficial relationship between the company and its personnel, with a strong commitment to employees so that they can always feel that they are doing what they do best, that they have everything they need to do so and feel properly rewarded.  I also believe in the implementation of systems for monitoring compliance with obligations, so that the plans established may be successfully achieved.

