          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb") I am Venezuelan-born and have two nationalities: Venezuelan and Spanish (I like to think I am a mix of the best parts of both cultures). I am a family man, happily married for twenty-nine years to María de los Angeles, a beautiful and exceptional woman in every sense, both inside and out. I have three children who are genuinely out of this world: Oliver, Oriana, and Aaron.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb") Thanks to my profession, I have lived in three different countries, I have had the opportunity to travel half the world, which has allowed me to engage with different cultures and hundreds of people from whom I have learned, among many things, that at the end we are all the same, we all face the same problems, suffer for the same reasons, want the same things in life and fear pretty much the same things.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb")  I consider myself a promoter of the importance of having a positive attitude in life (this is what my book is all about) and how this can be the main means of achieving much-desired happiness and, in worst case scenarios, allowing you to be fine in spite of the circumstances.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb")  I believe in family, moral values, hard work, two plus two will always equal four and that we should never stop laughing.  I exercise every day (running & gym) and I am always busy with a personal project. My hobbies include: flying RC plane models, writing, photographic and graphology. But, above all these, there is no doubt in my mind that the moments I enjoy the most are the ones I spend with my family.


